# Web Development Rules

## Required Reading

Before making ANY UI, component, page, or feature, read:

* docs/design.md
* docs/architecture.md
* docs/seo.md
* docs/product.md
* docs/skills.md

Treat those documents as the source of truth.

---

## Design Authority

docs/design.md is the primary authority for:

* colors
* spacing
* typography
* dark mode
* light mode
* layout
* buttons
* cards
* navigation
* page structure
* motion
* accessibility

Never invent alternative styles.

If design.md conflicts with generated code, design.md wins.

---

## Theme Rules

Dark mode is the default theme.

Requirements:

* Dark mode loads immediately.
* No flash of light mode.
* Store theme in localStorage.
* Respect saved preference.
* Light mode must also work.
* All components must support both themes.

Never ship components that only work in one theme.

---

## Visual Quality Rules

The UI must feel comparable to:

* Linear
* Vercel
* Raycast
* Resend
* Stripe Dashboard

Characteristics:

* Large typography
* Quiet interfaces
* Premium spacing
* Minimal shadows
* Strong hierarchy
* Subtle borders
* Calm animations

Avoid:

* Bootstrap appearance
* Generic Tailwind examples
* Bright gradients
* Marketing-site clutter
* Loud colors

---

## Astro Rules

Use Astro first.

Prefer:

* Astro components
* Static rendering
* Content collections
* Minimal hydration

Only use client-side JavaScript when interaction is required.

---

## Component Rules

Create reusable components.

Never duplicate large sections.

Use:

* Navbar
* Footer
* Hero
* FeatureCard
* ToolCard
* GeneratorPanel
* CalendarPreview
* FAQAccordion

---

## Mobile Rules

Every change must be tested for:

* 375px width
* 768px width
* Desktop

Never allow:

* horizontal scroll
* clipped cards
* overflowing text
* broken navigation

---

## SEO Rules

Every page must contain:

* title
* meta description
* canonical
* one H1
* FAQ section
* internal links

Tool functionality must appear above the fold.

---

## Performance Rules

Target:

* Lighthouse Performance 95+
* Lighthouse SEO 100
* Lighthouse Accessibility 95+

Avoid:

* unnecessary hydration
* large dependencies
* excessive JavaScript

---

## Before Finishing

Verify:

1. Design follows docs/design.md
2. Dark mode works
3. Light mode works
4. Mobile works
5. SEO structure exists
6. Components are reusable
7. No visual regressions
